# txtcmds sample guide
#
# txtcmds stores static output templates for command emulation.
# Each file name is the command (or command path), and file content
# is what Cowrie can return for that command.
#
# Suggested layout:
#   txtcmds/
#   └── examples/
#       ├── uname
#       └── id
#
# To activate a sample, copy it to txtcmds root using the command name.
# Example:
#   cp txtcmds/examples/uname txtcmds/uname
#
# Keep outputs realistic for your chosen distro and kernel version.
